cs.SI, cs.DM, cs.DB, cs.SD, cs.LG

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the analysis of real-world attributed graphs, which are a type of social network. 
- cs.DM (Data Mining) is also a likely category as the paper proposes a new method for mining structural correlation patterns in large attributed graphs. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is another possible category as the paper deals with the analysis of large datasets and proposes statistical significance measures to compare attribute sets against null models. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is less likely but still possible as the paper proposes an efficient algorithm for identifying relevant structural correlation patterns. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also less likely but possible as the paper proposes interestingness measures for evaluating the relevance of structural correlation patterns.
